# PopoverMenu

- [x] Done
- [ ] Close popover menus when clicking a non-submenu Item
- [ ] Fix handling/detection of submenu PopoverMenus (they should follow the Item tag, not be inside it (idx. 3, len = 4))

Each item must contain three tags: the icon, the label, and the ending (usually a shortcut or submenu indicator). All of them, except the label, are wrapped in a `span`. For an item representing a submenu, there is an extra tag being the sub-popover-menu.

```
<PopoverMenu>
  <Item>
    <span><Icon native={NativeIcons.INTERNET_EXPLORER}/></span>
    <Label>Internet Explorer</Label>
    <span>Ctrl+E</span>
  </Item>
  <Separator/>
  <Item>
    <span></span>
    <Label>Submenu</Label>
    <span><Indicator/></span>
  </Item>
  <PopoverMenu>
    <Item>
      <span></span>
      <Label>Item 1</Label>
      <span></span>
    </Item>
  </PopoverMenu>
</PopoverMenu>
```

